Sometimes in the winter ❄️ I can’t do a smoothie for breakfast. They set me up to be cold for hours. So, one of my favorite go-to warm breakfasts: @jordos_world pumpkin 🎃 protein waffles 🧇. Prepped a triple batch on Sunday and made 5 big waffles to have during the week. Topped with black cherry 🍒 Greek yogurt and lots of tart blueberries 🫐. Wonderfully filing, warming and the most delicious first meal of the day! They also freeze beautifully and reheat in the oven as good as the day you made them 😊 Just thought I’d share since PMS got me up and hour earlier than normal ☠️ The recipe is on her website and they are super quick to pull together. Happy baking! Love, BB #bbwellness #brookebrennanwellness

Good morning and happy Monday ❤️ It’s not a surprise that I love being in our kitchen- it’s the heartbeat of our home and the place I go to play 🤸🏼.
.
This week I cooked from, explored, experienced and fell in L❤️VE with @daniellewalker Healthy in a Hurry cookbook. Her recipes are always so delicious, but the concept of ease and quickness sold me on spending the week playing around with this 📖. A bonus for anyone with food sensitivities: each recipe is grain, gluten and dairy free!
.
Here are the recipes we made, in order and with the page number if you have the book and want to make them!
.
Sweet and Sour Pork (page 152): we loved the flavors in the sauce SO much on this! We grilled a pork tenderloin instead of cubing pork and adding to veg and sauce because our kids aren’t big on sauces yet. Absolute delicious and completely accessible on a busy weeknight.
.
Chicken and Apricot Stew (page 93): the tangine seasoning on the chicken thighs was insane!!! Also, we halved this recipe and still had plenty of leftovers. We went the pressure cooker route and it was so easy.
.
Stuffed Sweet Potatoes with Sausage and Blueberries (page 52): learned a new skill with this one- instant pot sweet potatoes are so easy and so creamy! Also, we are huge fans of the sweet and savory combo so adding blueberries 🫐 to the sliced @aidellssausage was 💯. I did one half with sausage and one with coconut yogurt, date sauce, 🍌 and @jemorganics .
.
My FAV was Sticky Green Onion Stir Fried Beef (page 185): this recipe was one of the best things I’ve ever eaten! The meat was like candy and I couldn’t stop eating it! Definitely hid these leftovers from Michael so that I could eat them 😉.
.
Brauts with Warm Potato Salad and Kraut (page 190): this made my German tastebuds sing with joy! Loved making this recipe for our date night in yesterday. We used pork chops instead of brauts because we had them on hand and it was delicious! That potato salad with crispy bacon 🤯 I could eat it daily!
.
Please check out this book if you are in a recipe rut- it’s was colorful, fun and definitely took me outside my comfort zone with flavors. Hope your day is just wonderful and happy cooking. Love, BB

the thickest chia pudding ❤️ #probiotic ,protein and #fiber rich to keep your body satisfied and happy for hours ⏳ also, you can #mealprep this one in advance so it’s ready + waiting for you which is the best!
.
1/2 cup @califiafarms 3 ingredient unsweetened almond milk
1/4 cup @backyard.buffalo probiotic strained yogurt
1/4 cup goat milk kefir
1/2 cup 0% greek yogurt
2 scoops @norcal_organic vanilla protein
2 tablespoons chia seeds
1 tablespoon ground flax
.
mix all the ingredients above and prepare your toppings!
.
added blueberries 🫐, raspberries, walnuts, almonds, raw pumpkin seeds, bee pollen, coconut shreds and cacao nibs to mine. The toppings absolutely make this!
.
here is the nutrition breakdown without toppings for you:
P: 46 grams
C: 25 grams
Fat: 19 grams
Fiber: 12 grams
Sugar: 10 grams
.
This has been the most nourishing meal to kickstart my day. Also, sometimes with a sweet smoothie or waffle 🧇 start my body just wants sweeter things all day. With this being less sweet I don’t have any sweets cravings which feels nice and balanced. I still ate chocolate 🍫 but just because I wanted to, not to answer a craving 😉 happy Friday, friends! #bbwellness #brookebrennanwellness #chiapudding #perimenopause

on repeat 🔁: yogurt + oat bowl
.
this has been my go to breakfast at home and on the road the last few weeks- it’s easy, delicious, keeps you full and has great fiber sources 🩵.
.
let’s do it: bottom layer is one package of maple brown sugar @betteroats with 1 tablespoon of chia seeds + enough hot water to create a creamy texture. let that sit and cool off a bit while you make the yogurt layer: 1 cup full fat greek yogurt, 1 tablespoon ground flax and one packet of @tryarmra unflavored colostrum (great for immunity and gut health). add the yogurt layer on top of the oats and top with berries 🫐 the oats give you all the sweetness you need!
.
this bowl packs 30 grams of protein and you hit 38% of you daily fiber recommendations while enjoying it!
.
will be making this in a few hours once I knock out my workout and walk with pepper 🐕‍🦺 happy thursday, bb #bbwellness #brookebrennanwellness #fiberfueled

This blueberry 🫐 chocolate 🍫 smoothie has been on repeat this week & I finally measured every ingredient out! It has superfoods, antioxidants, loads of protein and tastes like a chocolate milkshake 🥤

Good morning ☀️ and happy Monday 🩵 Was flipping through my pictures thinking about what I wanted to eat for breakfast and thought I’d share a few favorite meals on here with some thoughts 💭 
.
I read @drmaryclaire Galveston Diet, @dr.mindypelz Fast Like a Girl and @gorgeousesther See Ya Later Ovulator to learn about perimenopause lifestyle and nutrition recommendations to manage my symptoms.
.
Each meal is very thoughtfully planned to include protein (I usually eat about 120 grams a day), tons of plants 🌱, fiber, fats and some specific supplements. I have been cycle intermittent fasting, too, which energetically has been such a boost.
.
I wanted to dedicate myself to this process before my GYN appointment tomorrow where I hope to have a discussion around HRT. My symptoms are still very present and I am eager to find out if I can feel better with some support in that way.
.
The food has been delicious lately 😍 Lots of protein packed smoothies, @thepeachiespoon n’oatmeal, @madeline_moves protein crepes for breakfast// salads, stuffed bell peppers 🫑 or Greek yogurt bowls with veggies and animal protein for lunch// always something hot for dinner- again, animal protein and veggie sides.
.
Excited for tomorrow to meet with my doctor and fingers crossed we have some good dialogue around options. It’s so important to be your own advocate and I will be overly prepared with my notecards 👩🏼‍🏫
.
Off to the gym and hope you have a wonderful day! Any questions on specific meals just let me know 🩵 #bbwellness #brookebrennanwellness #perimenopause

Let’s whip up a fall 🎃 spiced, protein (54 grams!!!) pancake, shall we?
🍁
1 cup liquid egg whites
1 scoop @cleansimpleeats cinnamon roll protein
3 tablespoons organic pumpkin purée
1/4 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice
Vanilla bean paste/ extract 
Pink salt
🍁
Whisk all ingredients together and pour into a greased skillet. Cook slow and low so it doesn’t burn (also covered mine so it would cook faster!) I flipped mine, but you don’t have to once the top is set and cooked.
🍁
Mixed half a cup of @twogood vanilla yogurt with 1 tablespoon cream cheese to top the pancake. Also added blueberries 🫐, @lilys_sweets semi sweet chips, nuts/granola and this awesome salted caramel sauce (I can’t find the company but can send you the link. Just type “link” below and I’ll DM it to you)
🍁
This is fall on a plate and so delicious after a workout 🏋🏼‍♀️ or for an easy dinner when you want something hot but don’t want to work for it 😉
🍁
Happy Saturday! Love, BB

Top 10 favorite smoothie ingredients for a delicious, satisfying and healthy smoothie⤵️
1. Whey/dairy based protein: @cleansimpleeats brownie batter and vanilla 
2. Vegan/sensitive digestion: @lilsipper x @nuzest probiotic vanilla protein
3. Immune Support: @tryarmra colostrum

I was reminded of seasons in life and especially in parenting yesterday having a deep heart to heart with a dear friend. She’s a bit ahead of us with all her kiddos grown  and her wisdom just feeds my soul. We all need a person who you can bare your whole self to and know that the space is held. She also did a lot of solo parenting while her husband traveled and she understands the season I am in because she lived it. My parenting mantra has always been to make the ordinary extraordinarily 💫and last night it was just the three of us (plus pep). We planned a movie and I blew up the air mattress to make a giant watch space, put our first fire 🔥 on (even tho is was 76 outside) and we made a simple, but core memory together. I will be in my friends shoes in 8 years. Motherhood is my most true identity and I have just 8 more hands-on, hugs whenever I want, be there for all the good the bad and the in-between left. I vow to savor it. It is a season of challenge as they get older, but this time we pour into them, is the best gift we can give them. Fully present and fully available until they fly from our nest and make their mark on the world 🩵 Happy weekend from me to you, BB #bbwellness
